pageContext.claim: “Europe imposed draconian lockdowns, and yet their cases are exploding, their deaths are surging, and their economies are -- Let's face it. You look at what happened. They're in ruins.”
pageContext.analysis: There is no connection here. Unlike the United States, Europe managed to crush its first wave and was fairly open over the summer. Then the second wave came sooner in Europe than in the United States, requiring new restrictions, but the USA quickly caught up after the November election.
